node.text:
We caught up with the homie @rockinjellybean in Tokyo to talk about his origins, his mysterious mask, and his inspiration behind the new HUF x RJB collaboration. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The HUF x RJB Capsule Collection is now available worldwide. Grab your moms credit card and get yourself some titillating tees at the link in bio. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Video by @keitasuzuki_pd⁠⁠
Music by Jackie & The Cedrics - 'Rip It Out!'⁠⁠
#huf #rjb

Video by @woozygoldie 
Featuring @jimmygorecki @nappyfriedchicken @chicobrenes 
Narrated by @kingsteezbillion
Music by @tommyguerrero

node.text:
Keith and Spike Lee outside the HUF SF store, circa 2004. ⁠
⁠
The original HUF SF store attracted all walks of life. Skaters, sneakerheads, designers, artists, musicians, film directors… Keith kept the SF scene strong and we all wanted to be a part of it. ⁠
⁠
This Saturday our new SF store opens on 968 Valencia St. We're coming back to the city where HUF was born and where it belongs. We've said it once, we'll say it again. This one is for Keith. #KEITHFOREVER ⁠
⁠
📸: @photojoebrook

In 2002, @keithhufnagel opened up the first HUF boutique on an offbeat block in San Francisco’s Tenderloin district, bringing together the most respected skate, streetwear and sneaker brands under one roof.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
HUF quickly came to be recognized as the Bay Area’s institution for hard-to-come-by goods, attracting a new era of skaters, sneakerheads, artists, musicians and creatives. As it grew, Keith launched his own collection, creating a label he felt captured the spirit of skateboarding and street culture. The label is the HUF you know today.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
⁠⁠
San Francisco is where it all started. And on August 7th, we’re coming back to the city. Stay tuned. #KEITHFOREVER
